o feature</span><hr size=1> For a long time now I've agonized over PS6's undo feature, so I figured I'd ask about it in hopes of finding a solution.<br>
<br>
What irks me is the fact that if you select a layer, do something (like draw a line) and then undo that action, your layer selection gets reverted aswell. Many a time I've managed to mess things up by using the undo, forgetting that the layer selection got reverted and unknowingly drawing stuff on the wrong layer.<br>
<br>
Is there ANY way to stop PS from changing layers when you undo an action? Right now, I have to either suffer from re-selecting the layer if I undo something after changing the layer (and when you have tens, if not a hundred layers, it's a real pain), or I have to do something (erase an empty area, for example) every time I change the layer so that the next undo won't revert changes to layer selections.<br>
<br>
Either I'm blind to a checkbox to disable this &quot;feature&quot;, or then it's very well hidden (or quite possibly not even there).. Help! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><hr><b>Want to color my lineart?</b> Otherwise alter something I've created? Read my <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujspuonti.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><b>profile</b></a> for further information before proceeding!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukillersparrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Killer Sparrow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://raider56k.homestead.com/files/angif/fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/30/02 2:42:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4080.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://raider56k.homestead.com/files/angif/scorch.gif WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Q: Photoshop 6 and the undo feature</span><hr size=1> ...by pressing the undo only once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ...(j/k)<br>
Now, I didn't see what you meant the first time.<br>
Since the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> undo</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> feature works normal here<br>
(shortcut Ctrl + Z)<br>
<br>
But what you may have been doing is<br>
using the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Step Backward</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> option.<br>
(Alt + Ctrl + Z)<br>
Which result not only in deleting your previous action<br>
after you've selected another layer.<br>
It also reverts back to the previous layer.<br>
<br>
But other then the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> undo</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Step backward/forward</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
option can go back/forward multiple actions in the history.<br>
While the normal undo can only toggle back/forward<br>
between the last action.<br>
<br>
Anyway..if you just use the normal undo feature, it<br>
should solve your problem? <p><center><a target="_blank" href="http://animeprint.cjb.net"><img src="http://raider56k.homestead.com/files/icon/raiderbanner.gif" width=200 height=40 alt="Visit my Site" border=0></a>
